MoView version 0.0.1

MoView allows you to obtain most important movie data from imdb.com and choose what's worth watching tonight.

Final results list is rendered as index.html page placed in the MoView execution directory.

Installation:

- git clone
- python setup.py install

Note: before installation make sure that libxml2 and libxslt1 are installed.
They are needed for imdbpy module.

For  debian based linux you can add them using:
sudo apt-get install libxml2-dev
sudo apt-get install libxslt1-dev 

Usage:

moview file_name - extracts imdb data for a single movie

moview directory_name - extracts imdb data for a single directory

moview -r directory_name - extracts imdb data scaning recursivly all directories for direcotry_name

Please note: in the current version not recognized movies are not added to the results list rendered in index.html file.

Greetings:
MoView uses css template obtained from http://www.freecsstemplates.org 
MoVIew uses hash calculating method obatined from http://www.opensubtitles.org
imdb.com community for creating imdb python module

Enjoy!
